      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL SENOR (5) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where he gave a sight, finishing second (19.78) and beaten half a length over 350m at Grafton. Unbeaten from this box in two starts. Likely to feature again. LAURIE'S FERRARI (1) has been in sparkling form recording back to back wins, the latest at Gunnedah last time over 431m in (24.72). Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from four starts. Can measure up again. AUSSIE OSCAR (2) is a progressive type who recorded his 13th career win last time out (22.78) at this track. Solid record here at this trip including five wins. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Can make it two on the bounce. PAPER SHREDDER (3) is a last-start placegetter at this track and distance - should be thereabouts.",
